cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with syntactical fragments of second-order logic for characterizing the complexity of picture languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity classes of cellular automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses linear time recognition on nondeterministic cellular automata. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with picture languages of any dimension. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses hierarchy results and limits of logical characterizations.
